http://stackoverflow.com/questions/3961859/how-to-copy-to-clipboard-in-vim

you must have vim compiled with the +clipboard feature for ANY of the below 
suggestions to work in the first place! This is NOT the default on most systems

$vim --version 
显示的是 -clipboard就是默认没开启这个功能，如果是+clipboard就是开启了

archlinux debian ubuntu的源的vim默认没开启+clipboard功能，需要用xsel或xclip把
yank的复制进clipboard

进visual mode然后选中yank后
 :w !xsel -i -b   
就把yank的stuff传给clipboard了

:r !xsel -o -b
就把clipboard东西复制到当前buffer了，当然也可以用Shift-Insert

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

On Mac OSX

copy selected part: visually select text(type v or V in normal mode) and type :w !pbcopy
copy the whole file :%w !pbcopy
paste from the clipboard :r !pbpaste
On most Linux Distros, you can substitute:

pbcopy above with xclip -i -sel c or xsel -i -b
pbpaste using xclip -o -sel -c or xsel -o -b
-- Note: In case neither of these tools (xsel and xclip) are preinstalled on your distro, you can probably find them in the repos





